translated: Blomstrand, Gustaf Wilhelm, diocesan notary, Gothenburg, born on September 2, 1899 in Erode, British India, to a former missionary, and later church minister, Theodor B. and Hilda Carlison. Married in 1932 to Ingeborg Ekström. Children: Eva (born in 1934), Karin (born in 1935), and Christian (born in 1942). Graduated with a law degree from Lund University in 1927. Worked as a lawyer from 1927 to 1929, as a judicial assistant at Askim's court from 1929 to 1932, as an assistant to Gothenburg's Episcopal court from 1932 to 1937, and as a diocesan notary also at Gothenburg's Episcopal Court from 1937 onwards. Was a member in the diocesan council from 1933 onwards, chairman in the tax council from 1941 onwards, member of the city council from 1947 onwards, and chairman of the People's Party in Gothenburg from 1947 onwards.
